comment: Johnny is not an abuser in any way, shape, or form. He didn‚Äôt just decide in his 50‚Äôs to start beating on his wife. Yet, his wife, in her own words in her own voice has proven beyond all doubt, she is an abuser. This is also not a new tactic for her. Vanessa, Winona, Penelope, and all his other friends would not be defending him if they thought any of her ludicrous allegations held any merit. Abusers have deep internal issues. They start much sooner. I was in a violent situation for a little over two years. He was messed up in the head from childhood. AH is a liar. Not a good one, but a liar nonetheless. Her own recordings prove it. Texting about stabbing Johnny was truly terrifying to see. I have no doubt she would have, had the opportunity presented itself. Johnny is so lucky he got out alive. She will target the wrong meal ticket at some point. Then, her dream of being a DV victim will come true.  Physical bruises heal. The emotional and mental trauma leave scars forever. Some things change you permanently. Being used as a punching bag and being picked up by your head and thrown into doors and walls tend to leave deep mental scars. The only good thing was when I finally snapped and hit him back. The day I stood in the kitchen with a butcher knife daring him to try one more time and seeing the fear in his face, was the one true happy moment in those years of hell. I left that day. He stalked me for a few years, from the opposite side of the country, but I was so beyond done at that point. I will never be hit again. I hope Johnny is able to move past the trauma and finds real love with a real woman. He‚Äôs always seemed to be a very decent man. He didn‚Äôt deserve this cancer to infect his life.

I remember an incident when neighbours called police because on my then boyfriend . He was very violent to me but this night he was just verbally abusive.

"it looks like he has "
They had an idea he was violent but 25 years ago they could only arrest if you wanted to make a complaint .
I was 18 .With a young baby .
As much as I wanted him gone I was not going  to lie . Amber Herd makes me so mad . She makes out that shes so abused and scared .Yet her actions are opposite . Cheating ,hitting him and shouting at him are not what  someone does when being abused.
Thankfully my ex left me not long after this event with the cold sore .
For a 15 year old and moved in with her mum and her . He hit her once and her dad beat the living daylights out of him and he never did it again .

I want to Thank you for posting these videos! I KNEW from the start that such an aggressive woman... Not to say that Anyone can be a victim of Domestic Violence. But the reason I knew was because I was abused by my father. And then I turned around and became the Aggressive Domestic Abuser in my relationship/marriage just before I turned 19. He would later come crying, apologizing. I can tell you he knew of his temper, he‚Äôd gone to a voluntary psych ward for six months after striking my mother when he was 20. They married at 18 ( my brother was on the way when Mom was 17 ) So he never hit her but threw things. Screamed. It was walk on eggshells. He hit my brother and being 6 years younger I‚Äôd beg him to stop, I didn‚Äôt care if I got hit instead. The belt to my legs had me home from school for a week because we wore shorts in PE. Someone would have noticed. I should mention my Dad worked as an Electrician during the day and a police officer at night. He wanted better things for us. And today he takes medication. He didn‚Äôt drink, not ever until he was 45 and he sipped wine. He did know alcohol and his temper were too much. His temper among other things caused a stroke when he was 40. He was charming, respected and hard working. At 15 I dated a boy who shortly after turned 18. He brought me home 15 minutes after curfew and my father was waiting with other cops. I was arrested for curfew and the boy got contributing to the delinquency of a minor. The charges would later be dropped but he made his point. That night he‚Äôd found condoms in the boys truck. I was still a virgin and when we got home from the police station my Dad pulled me out of the truck ripping my shirt and backhanding me, calling me a slut.. I didn‚Äôt care anymore. You wanna hit me? Bring it on! Hit ME!! He later admitted that he thought I‚Äôd lost it permanently. He said Go to Bed. And another day off school. There‚Äôs more but As the Victim I was ashamed, I felt weak. I told Nobody. I was in karate so if friends noticed bruises I said Oh Karate. It was Father‚Äôs Day when he threw a huge family size laundry detergent at me from the top of 8 stairs, I‚Äôd carried the laundry down to the laundry room and was coming back for the freshly bought laundry soap. He threw it hitting my shoulder and knocking me on my ass. I ran 4 blocks to my best friends house, we lived in the country on a lake, expensive and my parents both worked two jobs. I took that all for granted, the swimming and fishing. Anyway I told my Best Friend and her Mom who was a counselor at the Orphanage and home for troubled children. She took me to the hospital for an X-ray. Cops were called and child services. I was given the option of the children‚Äôs home or go back home and they‚Äôd monitor me. My father moved me to a private school the very next day and I was forbidden to even talk to my best friend at all. Child services came to my school to talk for 45 minutes once a month. He didn‚Äôt hit anymore just verbal abuse, waking me up at 3 am on a school night if I‚Äôd left my shoes by the door and didn‚Äôt take them to my room. So I worked 40+hours a week as soon as I got my license, I‚Äôd had a job bussing and doing dishes from the age of 11. WORK was the religion in our house. I saved up and had an apartment arranged so on the day of my 18th birthday I could move in. March 1st. I was a waitress, cook at a pizza place. I kept this job for weekend nights and got a job at the same factory my mother worked at. I got out of school at 2:20 and was clocked in by 3:00. I always went in early to see my Mom. I resented her for never stopping my father and I almost got angrier at her in all if it but I Loved her for her never judging, she did try to help us hide things from my father, when I left -packed and hugging my baby sister good bye. She was 8 years younger. I went towards my father who glared at me. I softly told him if you touch my sister I‚Äôll take her. I‚Äôll find a way. He never hit her. He did lose it once much later
throwing a bowl and fork at her while she held my oldest daughter who was almost 2. I took my sister a lot over the years. comment:
"Then two years ago, I became a public figure representing domestic abuse."

Turd and her lawyers say she didn't specifically state "Johnny Depp" in her op-ed. However, that line clearly refers to the hoax she made against Johnny Depp in 2016. 

Prior to 2016, turd was NOT "a public figure representing domestic abuse." She was even the domestic abuser as proven by her DV arrest record in Seattle in 2009. Her op-ed in December 2018 on "The Washington Post" exemplifies this:

"Does the statement have the necessary ‚Äústing‚Äù to be actionable as defamation?
 
Not every false statement published about a person rises to the level of ‚Äúdefamation.‚Äù  The statement must have the ‚Äústing‚Äù of a reprehensible crime, or have inflammatory language or context so that the statement causes particular harm to one‚Äôs reputation, as to lower him in the estimation of the community or to deter third persons from associating or dealing with him, making the plaintiff appear odious, infamous, or ridiculous, or subjecting him to contempt, scorn, shame, or disgrace. Schaecher v. Bouffault, 290 Va. 83, 95, 772 S.E.2d 589, 595-96 (2015) citing Restatement (Second) of Torts ¬ß 559," 
(Source: https://www.robertslaw.org/summary-of-defamation-slander-libel-in-virginia/)

Not because "Johnny Depp" was not specified in her op-ed that was made in cahoots with the hypocritical "ACLU" and her "secret" lawsuit donors, it does NOT mean that she was not defaming him. Clearly, she and her turdian camp want to pull him and his career down.  

Defamation is a form of abuse. Turd and company are the ones who are abusive, NOT Johnny Depp.

comment: Anyone who was outraged against Johnny Depp in 2016 over these unsubstantiated allegations that Amber Heard made, should be equally (if not more) indignant now that there is verified proof she lied. She physically and emotional abused a innocent man and then tried to ruin him publicly with lies. She preyed on people's emotions and used real DA survivor's pain for her own gain. All the while, she was the perpetrator and not the victim. This is truly awful and heartbreaking. Even if you are not a fan of Johnny Depp this should be discussed and shared. Amber Heard should be made an example of and be fully exposed as a fraud to the world. Everyone canceled Johnny Depp without giving him a chance to defend himself. They took Amber's word and manipulated photos and edited video as proof without fact checking. She flaunted this hoax in front of everyone's eyes and people believed her and still do for some unfathomable reason. Johnny Depp has mountains of legit evidence that proves beyond a doubt that he was the victim of lies and abuse. If you believed Amber in the beginning because of your emotions then it's now time to admit you made a mistake and supported the wrong person. 87 surveillance videos, countless sworn depositions from witnesses that actual saw Amber assault Johnny or witnessed her carry out this hoax as it was happening, witnessed her without a mark on her anywhere, plus Amber Heard's own past arrest for domestic abuse, should be proof enough she is no victim. This was not a toxic relationship with mutual abuse and please don't make it out to be that because you're uncomfortable with the truth. Many have testified on Johnny Depp's behalf as to his character. He is not a violent person. In fact, he is the total opposite, kind, gentle and respectful to everyone he comes in contact with. He is one of the nicest celebrities to his fan's. He visits children's hospitals dressed up as Capt. Jack Sparrow often. All of his past partners have come out in defense of JD. He is greatly admired by everyone he has ever worked with. Most call him generous, a true gentleman and real professional. There is no pattern of violence on his side! He is not perfect and he freely admits his mistakes and past struggles with alcohol, but that doesn't mean he is abuser. Even if you don't care about Johnny Depp the actor/musician, even if you think he is strange, I implore you to take a step back and look at the facts and evidence with a rational eye. Think about the man and not the celebrity. This could be your dad, brother, friend or even you. Domestic abuse survivors are genderless. Let's support Johnny Depp and applaud him for his courage to come forward! He deserves our respect!
